Hi Brad,

Sounds like a fun trip!  I'm up in the Sacramento area and have been
thinking about taking a drive with my '71 along the coast.  This may
just be the kick I need to get everything together.  :)

I had the throttle cable break in the same spot on my '67 beetle just
over 20 years ago.  Snapped at a major intersection in San Francisco on
19th Avenue on my way back to Marin from Palo Alto.  Ugh.  I was on the
inside of 3 lanes and someone was friendly enough to use their
mini-truck to push me through the intersection and to a gas station on
the far corner, which wasn't required so much for the weight of the
vehicle, but because of the traffic pouring around us.  It's the
weirdest feeling when the engine is running and you have no control over
it with the pedal.

-John

