Well, our maiden voyage in "Betty Blue" the westy, went off pretty well,
but the trip was short.  Went to Big Sur via Hollister, Monterey, Carmel
by the Coast,  and down the Hwy1 via Big Sur to San Simeon, Cambria then
home via 101 to 198 to 33 (thru Coalinga) to 145 (back to Madera).
There isn't a lot of power on the hills which requires downshifting to
3rd.  For the most part, it holds the speed limit quite well.

Mechanically, everything went smoothly except one little hiccup on the
101 just after dark . . .the throttle cable broke!!!  Of all things!!
First time that's ever happened to me on any car.  The break was right
near the throttle body in the engine compartment.

<snip>
